240
00:12:06,333 --> 00:12:08,750
[MILLIANNA]
I'm so sorry, Kagura.

241
00:12:08,833 --> 00:12:10,250
[KAGURA] Unfortunately,
it seems I'm going

242
00:12:10,333 --> 00:12:12,041
to have to fight after all.

243
00:12:13,625 --> 00:12:16,000
We're so glad you could
join us! Let's go!

244
00:12:16,083 --> 00:12:17,791
Less talking,
more fighting!

245
00:12:17,875 --> 00:12:19,250
Wave!

246
00:12:22,541 --> 00:12:26,458
[KAGURA] Attacks that nullify an
opponent's magic? Impressive.

247
00:12:28,625 --> 00:12:32,041
[KAGURA] But against me...
it's pointless!

248
00:12:33,625 --> 00:12:35,958
This match is getting
intense, folks!

249
00:12:36,041 --> 00:12:37,833
[CHAPATI] Kagura doesn't
even have to draw her sword

250
00:12:37,916 --> 00:12:39,833
to lay the smack
down on her opponent!

251
00:12:39,916 --> 00:12:42,458
Heck, she's not
even using her magic!

252
00:12:42,541 --> 00:12:43,916
Wave!

253
00:12:46,250 --> 00:12:47,666
[KAGURA] Too slow!

254
00:12:52,000 --> 00:12:53,416
[cheering]

255
00:12:53,500 --> 00:12:55,500
Poor Yuka couldn't
even get in a single hit

256
00:12:55,583 --> 00:12:57,250
before he was knocked out cold!

257
00:12:57,333 --> 00:12:59,125
Lamia Scale's in trouble now!

258
00:12:59,208 --> 00:13:01,291
[CHAPATI] Looks like it's
gonna be Kagura versus Lyon

259
00:13:01,375 --> 00:13:03,208
in a one-on-one battle!

260
00:13:11,125 --> 00:13:13,583
[CROWD cheering]

261
00:13:13,666 --> 00:13:16,208
She defeated Yuka
without drawing her sword.

262
00:13:16,291 --> 00:13:18,750
She's more powerful
than I thought.

263
00:13:18,833 --> 00:13:20,583
Kagura Mikazuchi.

264
00:13:20,666 --> 00:13:22,750
It's clear that she's
a skilled fighter.

265
00:13:22,833 --> 00:13:25,250
She's not bad but I bet
she wouldn't last a second

266
00:13:25,333 --> 00:13:27,208
against my Iron Dragon Sword.

267
00:13:27,291 --> 00:13:28,666
[chuckles]

268
00:13:30,625 --> 00:13:33,416
Hey, do you think that
Lyon's gonna be all right?

269
00:13:33,500 --> 00:13:36,166
Well, I hope so, but he had
a hard time against Millianna,

270
00:13:36,250 --> 00:13:38,583
and now he's up against
Kagura, who's even stronger.

271
00:13:38,666 --> 00:13:40,250
[OHBA] Watch your tongue!
You have no idea

272
00:13:40,333 --> 00:13:43,333
what kind of power he has
buried under that cool façade.

273
00:13:43,416 --> 00:13:45,416
Lyon! Don't let that
stone-faced strumpet

274
00:13:45,500 --> 00:13:46,666
get the best of you!

275
00:13:46,750 --> 00:13:48,958
Make her pay for what
she did to poor Yuka!

276
00:13:50,083 --> 00:13:51,541
[KAGURA] I've heard
a lot about you.

277
00:13:51,625 --> 00:13:54,625
Apparently you once called
yourself the "Cold Emperor"

278
00:13:54,708 --> 00:13:56,583
and you performed a
dangerous ritual in

279
00:13:56,666 --> 00:13:59,000
the hopes of fighting
the demon Deliora.

280
00:13:59,083 --> 00:14:00,833
[LYON]
That was a long time ago.

281
00:14:00,916 --> 00:14:04,541
Now I'm just Lyon Bastia,
a wizard with Lamia Scale.

282
00:14:04,625 --> 00:14:06,500
Nothing more, nothing less.

283
00:14:06,583 --> 00:14:07,916
You know something?

284
00:14:08,000 --> 00:14:10,458
You remind me a lot
of myself years ago.

285
00:14:10,541 --> 00:14:12,916
But that's not a compliment,
because I was consumed

286
00:14:13,000 --> 00:14:15,625
by bitterness
and hatred back then.

287
00:14:17,083 --> 00:14:19,083
I have a question for you.

288
00:14:19,166 --> 00:14:20,375
[KAGURA] I noticed
that you never

289
00:14:20,458 --> 00:14:22,125
attacked Millianna directly.

290
00:14:22,208 --> 00:14:24,958
Were you holding back
just because she's a girl?

291
00:14:25,041 --> 00:14:26,791
Or were you worried
that in doing so

292
00:14:26,875 --> 00:14:29,375
you might reveal
your secrets to me?

293
00:14:29,458 --> 00:14:31,583
Good question.
Maybe you'll find out

294
00:14:31,666 --> 00:14:33,708
the answer during our battle!

295
00:14:33,791 --> 00:14:36,666
[LYON] Ice Make Dragonfly!

296
00:14:39,833 --> 00:14:41,833
[LYON] Ice Make Eagle!

297
00:14:44,833 --> 00:14:47,500
Just one swing and...
he's down!

298
00:14:47,583 --> 00:14:50,583
[CHAPATI] Can he get back up or
is this the end of the match?

299
00:14:50,666 --> 00:14:52,583
[GRAY] What the hell do
you think you're doing?

300
00:14:52,666 --> 00:14:54,916
And you call yourself
Master Ur's student!

301
00:14:55,000 --> 00:14:57,875
If she saw you right now,
she'd be completely embarrassed!

302
00:14:57,958 --> 00:15:00,833
C'mon, I know you can
do better than that!

303
00:15:02,333 --> 00:15:04,041
Are you going to attack?

304
00:15:04,125 --> 00:15:06,041
Because I thought
we came here to fight!

305
00:15:06,125 --> 00:15:07,708
I'm losing my patience!

306
00:15:07,791 --> 00:15:11,166
[LYON] Me, too. So let's
hurry and get this over with!

307
00:15:12,291 --> 00:15:15,375
[LYON] Ice Make Snow Tiger!

308
00:15:16,666 --> 00:15:19,708
And now, Ice Make Snow Ape!

309
00:15:20,750 --> 00:15:23,708
Ice Make Snow Dragon!

310
00:15:26,583 --> 00:15:28,250
I doubt that even
you are capable of

311
00:15:28,333 --> 00:15:30,208
avoiding three of them.

312
00:15:38,500 --> 00:15:39,666
[KAGURA] Do you
honestly think this is

313
00:15:39,750 --> 00:15:41,333
going to be enough to beat me?

314
00:15:41,416 --> 00:15:42,791
You're wrong!

315
00:15:52,000 --> 00:15:53,375
[BETH] Doggone!
There's her special

316
00:15:53,458 --> 00:15:55,291
gravity changin' technique!

317
00:15:55,375 --> 00:15:58,125
Yep! One of the many tricks
she's got up her sleeve!

318
00:15:58,208 --> 00:15:59,541
Normally she
doesn't use that move

319
00:15:59,625 --> 00:16:01,000
unless she's
feeling threatened.

320
00:16:01,083 --> 00:16:03,416
This Lyon must really
be challenging her.

321
00:16:03,500 --> 00:16:06,208
Wow. She's so powerful!

322
00:16:07,458 --> 00:16:09,083
[KAGURA grunts]

323
00:16:12,541 --> 00:16:13,916
[KAGURA] You're done for!

324
00:16:14,000 --> 00:16:16,041
[bell dinging]

325
00:16:16,125 --> 00:16:17,541
[MATO] You know
what that bell means!

326
00:16:17,625 --> 00:16:23,041
I'm afraid your time is up!
I declare this match a draw!

327
00:16:25,416 --> 00:16:27,166
[CHAPATI] You heard the man,
ladies and gentlemen!

328
00:16:27,250 --> 00:16:30,125
Looks like we've got yet
another draw on our hands!

329
00:16:30,208 --> 00:16:32,416
[BETH] Aw shucks!
But we were so close!

330
00:16:32,500 --> 00:16:33,500
[ARAÑA] Yeah, no kidding!

331
00:16:33,583 --> 00:16:35,416
She was just about
to finish him off!

332
00:16:35,500 --> 00:16:38,791
[LISLIE] Hey, a draw's better
than a loss. It's all good.

333
00:16:38,875 --> 00:16:40,750
If Kagura's okay with
how it turned out,

334
00:16:40,833 --> 00:16:42,250
then we should be, too.

335
00:16:42,333 --> 00:16:44,666
[SHERRY] I thought Lyon was
a goner for a second there.

336
00:16:44,750 --> 00:16:48,458
[SHELIA] Yeah. He was
literally saved by the bell.

337
00:16:48,541 --> 00:16:49,958
That numbskull
would've won the match

338
00:16:50,041 --> 00:16:51,833
if he didn't have
girls on the brain!

339
00:16:51,916 --> 00:16:53,208
He's in big trouble!

340
00:16:53,291 --> 00:16:55,708
Hope he's ready for a mighty
good spinnin' from me!

341
00:16:55,791 --> 00:16:58,125
'Cause that's just
what he's gettin'!

342
00:16:59,375 --> 00:17:01,875
[YUKA] Man, Kagura's
tough. Holy crap.

343
00:17:01,958 --> 00:17:04,416
Yes but something tells
me she's holding back.

344
00:17:04,500 --> 00:17:05,833
[YUKA] You may be right...

345
00:17:05,916 --> 00:17:07,875
but every year it's
the same story with her.

346
00:17:07,958 --> 00:17:10,125
Nobody's ever
seen her go all out.

347
00:17:10,208 --> 00:17:12,625
Sorry I let you down, Kagura.

348
00:17:13,541 --> 00:17:16,708
There's no need to apologize.
Lyon was strong.

349
00:17:16,791 --> 00:17:18,375
But If this had
been an actual fight

350
00:17:18,458 --> 00:17:20,208
rather than just a match...

351
00:17:21,583 --> 00:17:23,125
you would be dead.

352
00:17:26,000 --> 00:17:28,000
[KAGURA] You need to build
your strength, Millianna.

353
00:17:28,083 --> 00:17:29,916
So let's train even harder.

354
00:17:30,000 --> 00:17:31,458
[MILLIANNA] 'Kay!

355
00:17:31,541 --> 00:17:34,125
[CHAPATI] The crowd is still
going wild over our last match,

356
00:17:34,208 --> 00:17:36,791
but the next one is sure
to be just as exhilarating!

357
00:17:36,875 --> 00:17:38,416
That means it's our turn now!

358
00:17:38,500 --> 00:17:40,000
Yep! We're up!

359
00:17:40,083 --> 00:17:41,333
It's about damn time!

360
00:17:41,416 --> 00:17:42,208
Here we go!

361
00:17:42,291 --> 00:17:43,625
We're gonna
kick some ass!

362
00:17:43,708 --> 00:17:45,000
Please promise me
you won't get hurt

363
00:17:45,083 --> 00:17:46,750
out there, Natsu and Gajeel!

364
00:17:46,833 --> 00:17:48,958
No injuries! The last
thing I want is for

365
00:17:49,041 --> 00:17:51,500
[JUVIA] something bad to
happen to either of you!

366
00:17:51,583 --> 00:17:54,750
Why're you so worried
about them getting injured?

367
00:18:02,958 --> 00:18:04,833
Hm?

368
00:18:04,916 --> 00:18:07,833
Hey. Are ya feelin' any better?

369
00:18:10,458 --> 00:18:12,500
[LUCY] I'm getting there.

370
00:18:12,583 --> 00:18:14,083
Is your match about to start?

371
00:18:14,166 --> 00:18:17,541
Yep. And I'm gonna
win it for sure.

372
00:18:20,875 --> 00:18:23,125
Natsu?

373
00:18:23,208 --> 00:18:26,166
[inaudible dialogue]

374
00:18:31,250 --> 00:18:33,083
Sorry to burst in
on you like this.

375
00:18:33,166 --> 00:18:35,583
We just wanted to check on you
and see how you're feeling.

376
00:18:35,666 --> 00:18:37,083
Oh, hello, Natsu.

377
00:18:37,166 --> 00:18:38,541
Thanks for takin' care of her.

378
00:18:38,625 --> 00:18:40,000
I know she's in good hands.

379
00:18:40,083 --> 00:18:43,166
Sure! Good luck with
your match! Have fun!

380
00:18:43,250 --> 00:18:45,500
[CARLA] Oh my.
Look at that grin!

381
00:18:45,583 --> 00:18:47,458
What were you
two talking about?

382
00:18:50,708 --> 00:18:52,000
You ready to rock?

383
00:18:52,083 --> 00:18:54,291
All set! Now let's
go win this thing

384
00:18:54,375 --> 00:18:57,041
and make everybody
in Fairy Tail proud!

385
00:18:57,875 --> 00:18:59,416
[HAPPY] Natsu!

386
00:18:59,500 --> 00:19:02,166
[NATSU] Hey, Happy. What's up?

387
00:19:04,416 --> 00:19:06,750
[CHAPATI] And now, at long last,
we've come to the battle

388
00:19:06,833 --> 00:19:09,083
that everybody's
been waiting for!

389
00:19:11,833 --> 00:19:13,208
[CHAPATI]
One guild was considered

390
00:19:13,291 --> 00:19:15,958
the strongest in
Fiore seven years ago,

391
00:19:16,041 --> 00:19:19,083
and the other
currently holds the title.

392
00:19:19,166 --> 00:19:20,875
This is gonna
be a great match.

393
00:19:20,958 --> 00:19:23,125
It's Fairy Tail's
Natsu and Gahjeel

394
00:19:23,208 --> 00:19:27,208
versus Sabertooth's
Sting and Rogue!

395
00:19:27,291 --> 00:19:30,083
You're about to witness a
showdown of epic proportions!

396
00:19:30,166 --> 00:19:34,458
These aren't just any wizards,
they're Dragon Slayers!

397
00:19:34,541 --> 00:19:36,916
--[FROSCH laughing]
--[LECTOR] Go get 'em, Sting!

398
00:19:37,000 --> 00:19:39,708
[STING] I've been lookin'
forward to this all my life.

399
00:19:43,041 --> 00:19:45,750
[IGNEEL]
White dragon, Weisslogia.

400
00:19:45,833 --> 00:19:51,041
Shadow dragon, Skiadrum.
Who will emerge victorious?

401
00:19:51,125 --> 00:19:55,333
The Dragon Slayers you
raised or my Natsu?

402
00:19:55,416 --> 00:19:58,250
Have the humans
surpassed dragons?

403
00:19:58,333 --> 00:20:01,083
Or is that an
unattainable dream?

404
00:20:01,166 --> 00:20:03,708
Soon we will be
forced to take action.

405
00:20:03,791 --> 00:20:07,875
The Dragon King
Festival draws near.

406
00:20:11,000 --> 00:20:13,166
The crowd is gettin'
super hyped up!

407
00:20:13,250 --> 00:20:14,833
And I don't blame them!

408
00:20:14,916 --> 00:20:16,666
Go give "'em a
thrashin'," you guys!

409
00:20:16,750 --> 00:20:18,583
Get some hits in for us, too.

410
00:20:18,666 --> 00:20:21,208
Win this one for Fairy Tail!

411
00:20:21,291 --> 00:20:24,166
Sounds like they're about
to get started out there!

412
00:20:24,250 --> 00:20:26,666
I'm sure Natsu's gonna win.

413
00:20:26,750 --> 00:20:28,583
I have faith in him.

414
00:20:29,166 --> 00:20:30,375
[CHAPATI] This is it,
ladies and gentlemen!

415
00:20:30,458 --> 00:20:32,458
The Dragon Slayers
are on the battlefield!

416
00:20:32,541 --> 00:20:35,375
Now the only question is,
who will be triumphant?

417
00:20:35,458 --> 00:20:38,041
The fairies or the tigers?

418
00:20:38,125 --> 00:20:39,833
You face a formidable foe.

419
00:20:39,916 --> 00:20:42,416
You'll need to give it
everything you've got.

420
00:20:44,666 --> 00:20:47,541
[STING] All these years,
I've dreamed of fighting Natsu,

421
00:20:47,625 --> 00:20:49,916
and now I finally
get the chance.

422
00:20:54,291 --> 00:20:57,291
[MATO] Everyone's dying to find
out who's gonna win this round!

423
00:20:57,375 --> 00:20:58,416
No pressure!

424
00:20:58,500 --> 00:21:00,166
Remember, you've
got thirty minutes!

425
00:21:00,250 --> 00:21:03,291
Let the match begin!

426
00:21:03,375 --> 00:21:04,375
Ya ready?

427
00:21:04,458 --> 00:21:05,666
Yeah!

428
00:21:05,750 --> 00:21:07,125
Ugh!

429
00:21:07,916 --> 00:21:09,250
[NATSU grunts]

430
00:21:09,333 --> 00:21:16,458
♪

431
00:21:16,541 --> 00:21:20,083
White Dragon Roar!

432
00:21:20,166 --> 00:21:21,541
A laser?

433
00:21:27,625 --> 00:21:30,416
[ROGUE] Shadow Dragon Slash!

434
00:21:34,833 --> 00:21:36,250
[GAJEEL chuckles]

435
00:21:38,375 --> 00:21:39,583
[STING] Rogue!

436
00:21:39,666 --> 00:21:41,041
Ah!

437
00:21:43,333 --> 00:21:44,708
[grunts]

438
00:21:47,416 --> 00:21:50,208
[NATSU] Fire
Dragon Wing Attack!

439
00:21:50,291 --> 00:21:52,166
[CHAPATI] Whoa! I can't
believe what's happening

440
00:21:52,250 --> 00:21:55,208
right before my eyes! The
illustrious Sting and Rogue,

441
00:21:55,291 --> 00:21:57,625
the Twin Dragons of
Fiore's mightiest guild,

442
00:21:57,708 --> 00:22:00,208
have been overwhelmed
by Fairy Tail!

443
00:22:00,291 --> 00:22:01,916
You guys're tough,
that's for sure.

444
00:22:02,000 --> 00:22:03,416
Makes it more fun.

445
00:22:03,500 --> 00:22:04,916
Gajeel.

446
00:22:05,000 --> 00:22:06,916
Tell me somethin'.
Did you really defeat

447
00:22:07,000 --> 00:22:09,208
your dragons with that
measly power of yours?

448
00:22:09,291 --> 00:22:11,833
We didn't just "defeat" them.

449
00:22:11,916 --> 00:22:14,791
We killed our dragons
with our bare hands!

450
00:22:14,875 --> 00:22:17,208
[NATSU] But didn't you think
of them as your parents, too?

451
00:22:17,291 --> 00:22:18,833
[STING] That's none
of your business!

452
00:22:18,916 --> 00:22:21,666
But if you losers wanna see
our dragon-slaying power,

453
00:22:21,750 --> 00:22:24,500
I'll be happy to show it to ya!

454
00:22:24,583 --> 00:22:26,458
[STING] White Drive.

455
00:22:28,416 --> 00:22:30,166
[ROGUE] Shadow Drive.

456
00:22:32,833 --> 00:22:34,250
[grunts]

457
00:22:35,875 --> 00:22:37,333
[STING] Here we go!

458
00:24:13,083 --> 00:24:14,875
[NATSU] Finally! At long last!

459
00:24:14,958 --> 00:24:16,416
[HAPPY] It's here!

460
00:24:16,500 --> 00:24:17,625
[NATSU] It's my turn!

461
00:24:17,708 --> 00:24:18,916
[HAPPY] It's your turn!

462
00:24:19,000 --> 00:24:20,875
[HAPPY and NATSU]
To kick some butt!

463
00:24:20,958 --> 00:24:22,458
[NATSU] I don't care if
they're new-generation

464
00:24:22,541 --> 00:24:24,000
Dragon Slayers or whatever!

465
00:24:24,083 --> 00:24:25,416
I'm gonna wipe
the floor with that

466
00:24:25,500 --> 00:24:27,541
blond-haired bozo's stupid face!

467
00:24:27,625 --> 00:24:30,791
[HAPPY] Aw, yeah!
Go, Natsu! You can do it!

468
00:24:30,875 --> 00:24:33,583
[HAPPY and NATSU]
Next time: "Four Dragons!"

469
00:24:33,666 --> 00:24:36,083
[NATSU] And I'm gonna pulverize
those two dark-haired guys!

470
00:24:36,166 --> 00:24:37,333
You just watch me!

471
00:24:37,416 --> 00:24:39,875
[HAPPY] But one of 'em
is Gajeel. Oh, whatever.

472
00:24:39,958 --> 00:24:41,750
Good luck out there!

